Create new application from scratch:

a.) rails new 'app_name' -d postgresql

b.) see the database_name under database.yml file

c.) create the database under postgres, by default postgres is owner for database but we can set and update it by [alter database 'db_name' owner to 'owner_name']

d.) set username, password and host under database.yml file.

e.) further start working under rails c for create model,controllers etc.